  "The weight of the container pushing down on the gas": "",
  "Gravity pulling the gas particles to the container bottom": "",
  "Chemical reactions happening between the gas particles": "",
  "Gas pressure results from the countless collisions of gas particles with the walls of their container. More frequent or harder collisions mean higher pressure.": "",
  "What happens to the pressure of a gas when you decrease the volume of its container (at constant temperature)?": "",
  "Pressure stays the same": "",
  "Pressure increases": "",
  "Pressure decreases": "",
  "Pressure drops to zero": "",
