  "Volume stays the same": "",
  "Volume decreases": "",
  "Volume increases": "",
  "Volume drops to zero": "",
  "When temperature increases, gas particles move faster and push harder against the container walls, causing the gas to expand and take up more volume. This is described by Charles's law.": "",
