  "What is gas pressure?": "",
  "The force per unit area exerted by gas particles on the surfaces they contact": "",
  "The total number of gas particles contained inside a sealed container space": "",
  "The temperature at which a gas begins to turn into a liquid substance form": "",
  "The weight of all the gas particles measured in grams on a laboratory balance": "",
  "Gas pressure is the force per unit area exerted by gas particles as they collide with the surfaces around them. It is measured in Pascals, atmospheres, or other pressure units.": "",
  "What is Boyle's law?": "",
  "The law that states gas volume and temperature are directly proportional at fixed pressure": "",
  "The law that states gas pressure and volume are inversely proportional at fixed temperature": "",
  "The law that states mass is conserved in all chemical reactions inside a closed container": "",
  "The law that states energy cannot be created or destroyed but only transferred between objects": "",
  "Boyle's law states that for a given amount of gas at constant temperature, pressure and volume are inversely proportional — if one doubles, the other halves.": "",
  "What is Charles's law?": "",
  "The law relating gas pressure and volume at constant temperature conditions": "",
  "The law relating gas volume and temperature at constant pressure conditions": "",
  "The law stating that total mass is always conserved in chemical reactions": "",
  "The law describing how heat always flows from hot objects to cold objects": "",
  "Charles's law states that at constant pressure, the volume of a gas is directly proportional to its absolute temperature. When temperature goes up, volume goes up proportionally.": "",
